To use indipendent configs, I'm using aliases to lunch emacs. My .bash_aliases contains:

```
alias e="~/bin/shoot.sh emacs"
alias ep="~/bin/shoot.sh 'emacs -q -l ~/.emacs.python.el  --init-directory=~/.emacs.d.python'"
alias er="~/bin/shoot.sh 'emacs -q -l ~/.emacs.rust.el  --init-directory=~/.emacs.d.rust'"
alias ej="~/bin/shoot.sh 'emacs -q -l ~/.emacs.react.el  --init-directory=~/.emacs.d.react'"
alias ee="emacs -nw --no-splash"
alias ec="gnome-terminal -- emacs"
```

Note that you might have to preemtively create the init directories.
